grow it in the earth.

265
00:19:39,133 --> 00:19:42,400
This changed everything.

266
00:19:42,834 --> 00:19:44,767
Our ancestors did
something else they had

267
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:46,633
never done before.

268
00:19:46,767 --> 00:19:49,166
They invented new tools,
technology,

269
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:53,333
to plant and pull
food out of the earth.

270
00:19:54,033 --> 00:19:57,100
They settled down
and moved indoors.

271
00:19:57,667 --> 00:20:00,600
Our relationship to
nature, and to one another,

272
00:20:00,734 --> 00:20:03,300
would never be the same.

273
00:20:03,767 --> 00:20:06,166
This agricultural revolution,

274
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:09,133
the domestication of
plants and animals,

275
00:20:09,266 --> 00:20:12,433
is the mother of all
revolutions because all

276
00:20:12,567 --> 00:20:14,834
others trace back to it.

277
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:17,367
Its consequences
reach far beyond even our

278
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,834
own moment in time.

279
00:20:19,967 --> 00:20:21,800
Like most revolutions,

280
00:20:21,934 --> 00:20:24,867
this one brought
change that was both great,

281
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,600
and horrifying.

282
00:20:26,734 --> 00:20:30,533
There was a new concept
in the world, "Home."

283
00:20:31,734 --> 00:20:34,867
A specific place on the
planet where your ancestors,

284
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:38,300
and you, were born and lived.

285
00:20:38,767 --> 00:20:41,633
And over time these
settlements grew larger,

286
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:47,367
until about 20 cosmic seconds
ago or around 7000 BCE.

287
00:20:53,667 --> 00:20:56,100
Welcome to Çatalhöyük,

288
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:58,734
a community on
the Anatolian plain.

289
00:20:58,867 --> 00:21:01,967
It's about 9,000 years ago
and everyone has settled

290
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:04,200
in for the evening.

