00:30:50,266 --> 00:30:52,300
Spinoza's philosophy.

445
00:30:52,433 --> 00:30:56,166
This man, world famous for
finding a new law of nature,

446
00:30:56,300 --> 00:30:59,500
was often asked if
he believed in God.

447
00:30:59,633 --> 00:31:01,633
Albert Einstein replied:

448
00:31:02,233 --> 00:31:08,300
"I believe in Spinoza's God, who reveals
himself in the harmony of all that exists."

449
00:31:12,233 --> 00:31:15,500
Our understanding of nature's
laws has advanced far beyond.

450
00:31:15,633 --> 00:31:18,667
Spinoza's, and even
Einstein's wildest dreams.

451
00:31:19,967 --> 00:31:23,600
But there is one law of nature
we cannot seem to grasp.

452
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:27,033
Inscribed in the book of
nature is a parable about an

453
00:31:27,166 --> 00:31:29,800
ancient alliance
between two kingdoms.

454
00:31:30,533 --> 00:31:33,667
And those who
would tear it apart.

455
00:31:46,333 --> 00:31:48,967
Long ago,
there were two kingdoms.

456
00:31:49,100 --> 00:31:51,400
An alliance was
formed between them,

457
00:31:51,533 --> 00:31:54,533
one that would bring them
both riches beyond measure.

458
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:59,400
A partnership lasting more
than a 100 million years.

459
00:31:59,533 --> 00:32:03,700
And then a new kind of being
evolved in one of the two kingdoms.

460
00:32:04,233 --> 00:32:08,834
Its descendants plundered the
riches and violated the alliance.

461
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:12,567
In their arrogance, they
became a mortal danger to both

462
00:32:12,700 --> 00:32:15,500
kingdoms and to themselves.

463
00:32:27,166 --> 00:32:29,433
This parable is true.

464
00:32:29,567 --> 00:32:33,266
It's the story of two of the half
dozen realms of life on Earth,

465
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:36,467
the plant and animal kingdoms.

466
00:32:37,166 --> 00:32:39,967
It's not easy being green.

467
00:32:41,133 --> 00:32:44,600
Sex is challenging when
